TY  - JOUR
T1  - Validation of Contingency Model Leadership Training: Leader Match
AU  - Leister, Albert
AU  - Borden, Donald
AU  - Fiedler, Fred E.
Y1  - 1977/09/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255420
DO  - 10.5465/255420
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 464
EP  - 470
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the results of a study pertaining to an evaluation of a self-paced leadership training program called Leader Match. The method of training was based on the contingency model of leadership effectiveness and focused mainly on task performance. The training program produced better results in terms of overall task performance. The difference in personnel performance ratings was significant between those who participated in the Leader Match program and those who didn't. The study indicates that the training program increased the subject's motivation to perform better.
AB  - The article discusses the results of a study pertaining to an evaluation of a self-paced leadership training program called Leader Match. The method of training was based on the contingency model of leadership effectiveness and focused mainly on task performance. The training program produced better results in terms of overall task performance. The difference in personnel performance ratings was significant between those who participated in the Leader Match program and those who didn't. The study indicates that the training program increased the subject's motivation to perform better.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255420
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255420
