T1  - Communication in Administrative Bureaucracies
AU  - Bacharach, Samuel B.
AU  - Aiken, Michael
Y1  - 1977/09/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255411
DO  - 10.5465/255411
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 365
EP  - 377
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper examines the structural constraints on the frequency of both department head and subordinate communication within 44 local government bureaucracies. The effect of organizational size, shape, decentralization, routinization and boundary spanning on the frequency of both department head and subordinate communication were examined. The organizational variables explained 50 percent of the variance in the frequency of subordinate communication but little or none of the variance in the frequency of department head communication.
AB  - This paper examines the structural constraints on the frequency of both department head and subordinate communication within 44 local government bureaucracies. The effect of organizational size, shape, decentralization, routinization and boundary spanning on the frequency of both department head and subordinate communication were examined. The organizational variables explained 50 percent of the variance in the frequency of subordinate communication but little or none of the variance in the frequency of department head communication.
