T1  - A Critical Reanalysis of “a Test of two Postulates Underlying Expectancy Theory”
AU  - Liddell, William W.
AU  - Solomon, Robert J.
Y1  - 1977/09/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255419
DO  - 10.5465/255419
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 460
EP  - 464
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a commentary on the article ?A Test of Two Postulates Underlying Expectancy Theory,? by F. A. Starke and O. Behling. In the original article Starke and Behling attempted to test the transitivity and independence properties of an expectancy model. The authors contend that they instead reported another methodologically faulted test of the model's ability to predict behavior. They explain that part of their test of the independence postulate was inappropriate and their remaining evidence is questionable.
AB  - The article presents a commentary on the article ?A Test of Two Postulates Underlying Expectancy Theory,? by F. A. Starke and O. Behling. In the original article Starke and Behling attempted to test the transitivity and independence properties of an expectancy model. The authors contend that they instead reported another methodologically faulted test of the model's ability to predict behavior. They explain that part of their test of the independence postulate was inappropriate and their remaining evidence is questionable.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255419
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255419
Y2  - 2026/04/24
